metadata.name: Chaotic Neutral #59
metadata.description:
'Chaotic Neutral' by pixelwank 
A fun mixture of 10print inspired patterns, spiralling shapes and masking. 

Sometimes more minimal, often chaotic and maximal.

I wanted this work to be confronting at times, make the viewer zoom in and get lost in the chaos. 
And on the flipside, zoom out and let the eyes wander around the piece, guided by the motion of the patterns and feel a sense of calm.

Variety of palettes, grid sizing, strokeweights, blendmodes and more. 

5 possible aspect ratios with 3:4 being most common. 

10% of primary sales are going straight to the Waiting To Be Signed wallet as a donation and thankyou for always delivering great content on the fxhash ecosystem with their podcast <3

50% of royalties to the minter. 
In live mode press 's' or 'S' to save higher resolution image. Contact me via twitter if you want a super hi-res file. 

Copyright pixelwank 2022.
Made with love and p5js 

Thanks for collecting!
Big shoutout to the Circolors fam. Don't worry something's cooking <3 

Remember. It's. For. Fun.
R.I.F.F. 
<3

metadata.name: GuilCity #71
metadata.description:
GuilCity is the beginning of an exciting journey bringing Guillaume Cornet‚Äôs densely-packed cities into the generative realm with the help of Matthew‚Äôs (@frostbitten‚Äôs) magic touch.

Matthew‚Äîwith his background in coding and animation‚Äîenables a new opportunity to experience these cities like never before. Numerous elements from vehicles to characters and even architecture have been given life. Interact with the city (computer mouse only): poke and peek around (even behind) in this active search & find journey! 

Each generative city fills the composition with the type of whimsical, expressive elements and characters you‚Äôve come to know Guil for. What kinds of wacky features have you discovered yet?

‚Äî

The tech behind this project utilizes the highly compressed WEBP image format in order to provide so many full-color options. This format is great, but unfortunately Safari on desktop/laptop must be upgraded to at least version 14 and macOS to at least version 11 Big Sur to use it.

The animation system for this project was created from scratch with additional help from the PIXI.js library for individual mesh animations.

‚Äî

To find out more about your GuilCity, copy your unique operation hash and place it at the end of the following url:
‚Ä¢ https://my.guil.city?fxhash=
(for example: https://my.guil.city?fxhash=ooezL8cffNJGSc4TfNQp3u3WnDpkg8J3zFRczLuumceoYU5QYPs)

‚Äî


The entire process has been a learning experience for both of us, adapting and exploring the many possibilities to interact with each others‚Äô skills and ideas.

We really enjoyed building this project together and are excited as we invite you to take a dive into your very own urban playground!

Merci √† tous! Cheers!
  - Guillaume Cornet, Matthew Seremet

metadata.name: Elemental walks II #17
metadata.description:
"Elemental walks II" is an extended exploration of the interaction and perception of different systems. The generated double grid pattern, the first system, transforms into a crowd of random walkers, this second system moves in random but constrained ways, and with each movement a third system is generated: the texture.

Use the 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 keys to switch between 5 states of movement within the dynamic pattern, you can pause ('p'), speed up ('+') or slow down ('-') the movement. 

Click on the canvas and the colours change within the composition.

'r' to reset position or release the walkers
'p' to toggle pause/play

'1' for vertical movement
'2' for diagonal movement
'3' for horizontal movement
'4' for a second diagonal movement
'5' for vertical and horizontal movement

'-' to slow down
'+' for faster movement

's' save png
'j' save jpg

metadata.name: Nounfall #119
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: Letters to young poets #140
metadata.description:
every hash generates a unique visual poem out of 279,720 possible combinations by mending 4 of 81 png layers created by saami heyes and merchant coppola. 

the combinations construct new context, starting a dialogue between the layers, sometimes creating new meaning, sometimes creating new nonsense.


Code supervision by Liam Egan (@neuromantic6)

metadata.name: StairWaves #77
metadata.description:
StairWaves is a generative collection imagining abstract stairs built in a wavy nature, with shadows being a key theme. While some waves are quite turbulent, others are just flat.

All shapes in the artwork are built using the same core logic applied in different ways. The method used to draw the waves is also used to draw the shadows, as well as the subtle textures on the surface of the waves. This homogeneous approach ensures a consistent and flowy feel to the final output.

StairWaves is coded entirely in p5.js. 

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: Sand Flow #112
metadata.description:
bstract generative art that simulates sandpainting.

"Sandpainting is the art of pouring coloured sands, and powdered pigments from minerals or crystals,
or pigments from other natural or synthetic sources onto a surface to make a fixed or unfixed sand painting.
Sand paintings have a long established cultural history in numerous social groupings around the globe."

Created from 100% code and math.

(Generation time is a little longer on this work (10-15 sec.), please be patient)

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px

Created using p5js.

@Mutart, May, 2022.
